# Production Environment Variables
# For Digital Ocean App Platform deployment

# Database Configuration (Digital Ocean Managed PostgreSQL)
# Get this from your Digital Ocean database connection string
# Format: postgresql://username:password@host:port/database?sslmode=require
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@db-postgresql-nyc3-12345-do-user-67890-0.db.ondigitalocean.com:25060/defaultdb?sslmode=require

# Node Environment
NODE_ENV=production

# Next.js Configuration
NEXT_TELEMETRY_DISABLED=1

# Application Port (usually 3000 for containerized apps)
PORT=3000

# DIGITAL OCEAN DEPLOYMENT NOTES:
# ================================
# 1. In Digital Ocean App Platform, add these as environment variables:
#    - DATABASE_URL: Use the connection string from your managed PostgreSQL database
#    - NODE_ENV: Set to "production"
#    - NEXT_TELEMETRY_DISABLED: Set to "1"
#
# 2. To get your DATABASE_URL from Digital Ocean:
#    - Navigate to your database cluster
#    - Click "Connection Details"
#    - Copy the "Connection String" (make sure SSL mode is enabled)
#
# 3. Database Migrations:
#    - Run migrations manually before deploying: `bun run db:push`
#    - Or add a pre-deploy script in your CI/CD pipeline
#    - Do NOT run migrations automatically in the app startup (production best practice)
#
# 4. Security Best Practices:
#    - Never commit .env files with actual secrets to git
#    - Use Digital Ocean's encrypted environment variables
#    - Rotate database credentials regularly
#    - Enable SSL/TLS for database connections
#
# 5. Testing Production Config Locally:
#    - Create a test managed database on Digital Ocean
#    - Use .env.prod for local production testing
#    - Run: make test-prod
